name: reduced sodium broccoli beef
instructions:
1. Mince garlic cloves and dice tomato. 

2. Cut beef into thin strips.

3. Defrost frozen broccoli in microwave.

4. In a large skillet heat oil and sauté the garlic.

5. Add broccoli and stir-fry until cooked. Remove from pan and set aside.

6. In same skillet add sliced beef and cook through.

7. In a small bowl combine chicken broth, cornstarch and soy sauce.

8. Add cooked broccoli, sauce and tomato to the pan with the beef.

9. Heat and stir until sauce is thick.

10.	Slice green onions and garnish prior to serving.
